#. module: real_estate_management
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:real_estate_management.report_contract_document
msgid ""
"<strong>Eight. Rent update.</strong>\n"
"                        The rent may only be updated on the date on which each\n"
"                        year of the contract's validity is fulfilled, by\n"
"                        reference to the annual variation of the\n"
"                        Competitiveness Guarantee Index, capped at the\n"
"                        variation of the Consumer Price Index (CPI). The\n"
"                        updated rent shall be enforceable from the month\n"
"                        following written notification to the Lessee."
msgstr ""

#. module: real_estate_management
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:real_estate_management.report_contract_document
msgid ""
"<strong>Eleven. Conservation of the dwelling.</strong>\n"
"                        The Lessor undertakes to carry out, without the right\n"
"                        to raise the rent for this reason, the repairs\n"
"                        necessary to keep the dwelling in conditions of\n"
"                        habitability, except those that result from\n"
"                        deterioration attributable to the Lessee, their\n"
"                        dependents or visitors, by action, omission or\n"
"                        negligence. After the first five (5) years, the Lessor\n"
"                        may carry out improvement works, which shall entitle\n"
"                        them to raise the rent with the limitations provided\n"
"                        by the LAU."
msgstr ""

#. module: real_estate_management
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:real_estate_management.report_contract_document
msgid ""
"<strong>Fifteen. Conflict resolution.</strong>\n"
"                        For the resolution of any conflict that may arise from\n"
"                        the interpretation of this contract, the parties\n"
"                        submit to the ordinary jurisdiction."
msgstr ""

#. module: real_estate_management
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:real_estate_management.report_contract_document
msgid ""
"<strong>Five. Lessee's withdrawal.</strong>\n"
"                        The Lessee may withdraw from the contract once six (6)\n"
"                        months have elapsed since its signing, with at least\n"
"                        thirty (30) days written notice. In such case, the\n"
"                        Lessee shall compensate the Lessor with an amount\n"
"                        equivalent to one monthly instalment of the rent in\n"
"                        force for each year remaining, or its proportional\n"
"                        part if the period is less than one year."
msgstr ""

#. module: real_estate_management
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:real_estate_management.report_contract_document
msgid ""
"<strong>Four. Down payment.</strong>\n"
"                        The Buyer has delivered"
msgstr ""

#. module: real_estate_management
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:real_estate_management.report_contract_document
msgid ""
"<strong>Four. Lessor's right to recover the dwelling.</strong>\n"
"                        The Lessor states that the obligatory extension of this\n"
"                        contract shall not apply if, after the first year has\n"
"                        elapsed, they communicate the need to occupy the leased\n"
"                        dwelling before five years have passed, for permanent\n"
"                        housing for themselves, first-degree relatives by\n"
"                        consanguinity or adoption, or for their spouse in cases\n"
"                        of final judgment of separation, divorce or matrimonial\n"
"                        nullity. Such communication shall be made in writing\n"
"                        with two (2) months notice."
msgstr ""

#. module: real_estate_management
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:real_estate_management.report_contract_document
msgid ""
"<strong>Fourteen. Resolution of the contract.</strong>\n"
"                        Breach of any of the clauses of this contract and, in\n"
"                        its absence, of the regulations applicable, shall be\n"
"                        cause for resolution of the contract for either party."
msgstr ""

